Additional EDA to explore the effect of removing outliers using the "standard" Q1-IQR1.5 to Q3+IQR1.5

In [1]:
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib as mpl
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.image as mpimg
import seaborn as sns
In [2]:
AirBnB = pd.read_csv("AB_NYC_2019.csv")

Boxplot price

In [3]:
f, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 8))
fig = sns.boxplot(AirBnB['price'])
fig.axis(ymin=0, ymax=500);

Now find the actual values for min and max so we can exclude the outliers

In [4]:
AirBnB.price.describe()
Out[4]:
count    48895.000000
mean       152.720687
std        240.154170
min          0.000000
25%         69.000000
50%        106.000000
75%        175.000000
max      10000.000000
Name: price, dtype: float64

Median = 106

Q1 = 69

Q3 = 175

IQR = 175-69 = 106

IQR * 1.5 = 159

Min = 106-159 = 0 (the lowest in our dataset). I suggest we still discount "0" as an outlier

Max = 175+159 = 334

New York range = 1 - 334

In [5]:
New_York_no_outliers = AirBnB[(AirBnB['price'] > 1 ) & (AirBnB['price'] <= 334 )]

In [8]:
coordinates = (-74.2623, -73.6862, 40.4943, 40.9144)

plt.title('Properties with outliers removed')

fig.axis(ymin=0, ymax=500);

Create a subset for each neighbourhood group

In [15]:
Manhattan_no_outliers = AirBnB[(AirBnB['neighbourhood_group'] == 'Manhattan') & (AirBnB['price'] > 1 ) & (AirBnB['price'] <= 407.5 )]
Brooklyn_no_outliers = AirBnB[(AirBnB['neighbourhood_group'] == 'Brooklyn') & (AirBnB['price'] > 1) & (AirBnB['price'] <= 285 )]
Queens_no_outliers = AirBnB[(AirBnB['neighbourhood_group'] == 'Queens') & (AirBnB['price'] > 10 ) & (AirBnB['price'] <= 200 )]
Staten_Island_no_outliers = AirBnB[(AirBnB['neighbourhood_group'] == 'Staten Island') & (AirBnB['price'] > 13 ) & (AirBnB['price'] <= 200 )]
Bronx_no_outliers = AirBnB[(AirBnB['neighbourhood_group'] == 'Bronx') & (AirBnB['price'] > 1 ) & (AirBnB['price'] <= 180 )]

Now concatonate them back into a single dataframe

In [16]:
consolidated_no_outliers = pd.concat([Manhattan_no_outliers, Brooklyn_no_outliers, Queens_no_outliers, Staten_Island_no_outliers, Bronx_no_outliers])
